reviews.text: Station is a bit worn out, but the major problem here is the Hammersmith & City line. If I remember correctly it is from either Platforms 2, 3 or 6. Passenger beware!
Since I was born in Barking, I guess I'll always have a fondness for the place. It's certainly no where near as bad as some people would lead you to believe! :-)

Managed by #C2C, it's possibly #TFL's worst station in terms of staff, crowd control and management. Oh staff is there during rush hours but only to stand by and do nothing. Rush hour is a daily nightmare. There is no exit or entrance management. There is filth and dirty water everywhere.  Utterly shambolic!

Ok well I’m rating it two star because the station is just dirty and trash plus the overground is one of the most rubbish service I’ve ever seen for having a 8 platform station it should be clean with step free access and good train services overall the whole place needs a massive upgrade right now!
The lift is not working for a week now
